The Rulzeans are incredibly genetically diverse, especially considering they are still capable of interbreeding and thus could be argued to still be of the same species. For example, the more common Northern Burrowers have an average height of between 180 to 190 centimetres, whilst their Seltran cousins stand significantly taller, with an average height between 260 and 270 centimetres. The factbook mentions that interbreeding between these 'species' results in "minimal physical or genetic issues", but how commonplace are such pairings in the first place? Are genetic issues common, even if they are not particularly problematic?
